				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Hmm well...  Though I agree that a WAR can technically be either a sword and a shield, if forced to classify, I'd say shield...
<br />

<br />
If all characters are doing their jobs, at Lv. 30, where would you rate the characters damage per minute, in comparison to other classes.  He's outdamaged by BLMs, DRKs, SMNs, RNGs, THFs, RDMs, SAMs, NINs, BSTs, and over time, MNKs.  There aren't too many people that can't out-damage a WAR.  If you're thinking of starting the game, and you want to be the character that really takes the health down on a monster, then WAR I think would not be for you.  Yes, you'll hit the monster in addition to provoking, but more or less everyone expcept the WHM will hit harder than you will.  If you like the melee aspect, and you want to be a sword, and not a shield, consider DRK, or even SAM.  If you don't mind magic, try being a BLM, you'd be suprised the massive amounts of damage you'll do once you learn elemental weaknesses by heart, and how to MB off of skillchains.  RNG is really fun too...  There's a whole plethora of "swords" out there, and very few shields...  WAR, just happens to be, in my opinion, a shield, and a good one.  Only thing that tops it, is a Blink-tank, and a PLD.  I find, at around 30 I'll see WARs, using a 1-handed weapon, hitting the mob for 10-20 damage usually...  THFs will SA, and TA, for maybe 400 dmg within the first 30 secs...  The BLMs doing 60-100 per nuke, and RNGs hitting 75+ consistently...  Yes, you're damaging it, but you're not the one taking the noticeable chunks out of its health...  Esp. crab enemies and the like that have the dreaded Metallic Body, etc.  And yes, equipment does make the man...  But, like it was stated earlier, most WARs are new, and strapped for cash.  Equipment makes up a good bit of what kind of WAR you are, but if you're the tank, don't berserk.  Simply because, you're the "shield" not the "sword."  I've kicked many WARs from my parties simply because they insisted on using Berserk, and it made it a hell of a lot harder to keep his health up for me, being that his DEF was reduced.  When there is more than one tank, and you're not the main one, then Berserk is alright, making you slightly more of a "sword."  Just remember, that if you're the only WAR, chances are that you're a tank, and you're going to take the hits, and you're not going to deal all that much damage...  That's the reason you have voke, cuz the monsters get pissed at the little BLM that's nailing it for 5X as much as you are.  But yea, that's just my opinion on the matter.
<br />

<br />
Pretty much, you're the Marine, on the front-line...  And the BLMs are the Air Force, ready to napalm them once they're focused you!   <img src="images/smiles/icon_twisted.gif" alt="icon_twisted.gif" border="0" /></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
