			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Warrior is just a shield?
<br />

<br />
Oh really? Time for some education! 
<br />

<br />
Hit for hit, the only thing Dark Knights have over Warriors is a few extra attack bonuses. They have equal Strength, Dexterity, and Great Axes and Scythes have very close damage ratings.
<br />

<br />
However, Warriors come blessed with the best melee abilities in the game. Berserk is God-sent. 25% boost in attack 3/5 of the time makes a huge difference. Double Attack can effectively make them attack twice and work in WSes as well. You can potentially do a 10 hit Pentathrust. Let's face it-Double Attack rocks. At 35, we get Warcry, which is decent. It is about as effective as Last Resort, but on the whole party. Not great, but it helps. At 45, we get Aggressor. Every single other melee job wants this, but can't. This works like Berserk, except raises Accuracy and lowers Evasion. Using it before a multi-hit WS practically ensures all hits will in fact hit the mob.
<br />

<br />
With the exception of Soul Eater, DRK abilities suck. Last Resort is lame, it acts like Provoke and adds LESS attack boosts than Berserk and lasts 1/10 of the time. It can only really be used for a slight boost before a WS. Soul Eater is THE defining Dark Knight ability. Any DRK that doesn't use Soul Eater should switch to Warrior. Any DRK that abuses Soul Eater will end up dead. It is very tricky to use, but when used properly, it sends you damage output through the roof. Is it enough to make DRK more powerful than Warrior? If subbing Warrior and used properly, yes. At certain points in the game, that is. Until level 50, Double Attack can make up for this. At 45, Warriors get an ability DRKs can never get, Aggressor. From 50 on, an extremely good Dark Knight can overpower a Warrior, but there aren't many of those around. And that is not including WSes.
<br />

<br />
Weapon skills: Warriors get better Weapon Skills. The Breaks=Secks. Rampage=Secks. When DRKs get Guillotine, Warriors gets Raging Rush. DRK WSes SUCK until level 60. Even then, Raging Rush and Guillotine are about equal. Seriously, Slice is their most powerful one for a large portion of the game. Dark Knights can use a Great Axe to try to offset this, but they can't do it as effectively. Dark Knights have to sub Warrior to be effective, missing out on Sneak Attack. And until level 50, there is absolutely no chance of getting the Four-hit OMGWTF 1,000 damage Sturmwind. Once they reach level 3 skillchains, DRK will do more damage on the WS. However, DRKs pretty much need to sub THF from then on and Warriors will therefore do a lot more damage otherwise. From 65/66+, DRK/WAR&gt;WAR&gt;DRK/THF in pure damage, and WAR=DRK/WAR=DRK/THF as a whole package.
<br />

<br />
On a side note, DRKs and Warriors don't need to get competitive. Warriors and DRKs go hand in hand as SC partners. Early levels include: Shadow of Death &gt;&gt; Sturmwind (Fragmentation) then later on Vorpal Scythe/Power Slash &gt;&gt; Rampaging Axe (Distortion), then at 60, Guillotine &gt;&gt; Raging Rush (Fragmentation again), and finally up high Mistral Axe &gt;&gt; Spinning Slash (Light SC). Warrior and Dark Knight are the perfect team. They can fight anything effectively at any point in the game. Throw in Paladin and you've got an unstoppable force.
<br />

<br />

<br />
And one more thing: At higher levels, it gets difficult to tank as a Warrior. Warriors get a D in Vitality, hell even Dark Knights get higher than that. What Warrior DOES get is Provoke. Provoke allows them to sub more tank-worthy subjobs, like Monk and use it to its advantage. Monk, in theory, would make an awesome tank. HP of Gods, tied with Paladin for the highest VIT, Counter, etc. etc. etc. etc. Even Dodge helps! Their problem is that they get paper armor. Warriors can sub Monk and get all their advantages, but have the ability to equip heavy armor. Or they could sub Ninja and have blink at their disposal. Other jobs can't do this to tank since they do not have Provoke. While a Warrior tank is plausible, it gets difficult at higher levels. You pretty much have to be a Galka to make a great Warrior tank, but it can be done. AntiMatter has been talking about this for a while, we really want to test out a WAR/MNK tank 1-75. We strongly believe that it can work out! The thing is, Warrior usually makes a much more efficient DD. Dark Knight could probably make a decent tank with higher VIT than WAR, heavy armor, and Drain, but it isn't as effective as just going DD.
<br />

<br />
You caught me, Warrior is my favorite job. I just love everything about it. In my eyes, Warrior is the perfect melee job.
<br />

<br />
Note: This is a comparison between DRK and WAR I wrote on another forum. I just copied and pasted it from there.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
